##  My Personal Reflection

In my career, Iâ€™ve seen how **underestimating impact** can lead to disaster.

Example: At a former organization, leadership dismissed a known vulnerability as â€œlow riskâ€ because â€œno one would attack us.â€ Six months later, the system was breached â€” leading to public embarrassment and a costly recovery.

Lesson learned:

**Always respect the â€œwhat ifâ€ â€” and validate assumptions with reality.** 

